            <unittitle><persname>Robert Shelton MacKenzie</persname>to Dear
                  Sir</unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1863 Jan 15</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>2 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Is sending some copies of 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Press</title></bibref>and promises to send the articles he is
                  writing about 
                  <persname>James Sheridan Knowles</persname>;
                  discusses 
                  <persname>Joachim Hayward Siddons</persname>' article
                  in 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Harper's</title></bibref>and his claim that he is the illegitimate
                  son of 
                  <persname>George Siddons</persname>, a son of 
                  <persname>Sarah Kemble Siddons</persname>; MacKenzie
                  doubts this claim and says his real name is
                  Stackquelar (sic).]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
      </c01>
